issues.solution:
Maintain an allowlist of permitted origins and reject connections whose request.origin is not in it. Example:
const ALLOWED_ORIGINS = ['http://localhost:8080'];
if (!ALLOWED_ORIGINS.includes(request.origin)) {
  request.reject(403, 'Forbidden');
  return;
}
const connection = request.accept(null, request.origin);

Replace 'var' with 'const'/'let'. Migrate from 'websocket' to 'ws' (npm install ws). Example modern server:
import { WebSocketServer } from 'ws';
const wss = new WebSocketServer({ port: 1337 });
wss.on('connection', (ws, req) => { ... });

Use filter on the clients array instead of splice-by-index:
connection.on('close', () => {
  clients = clients.filter(c => c !== connection);
});

Skip the originating connection during broadcast:
for (const client of clients) {
  if (client !== connection) client.sendUTF(json);
}

Add event handlers:
this.socket.onerror = (err) => { this.status = 'error'; console.error(err); };
this.socket.onclose = () => { this.status = 'disconnected'; this.scheduleReconnect(); };

Guard the send call:
if (this.socket && this.socket.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {
  this.socket.send(...);
}

Use an environment variable:
const WS_URL = process.env.VUE_APP_WS_URL || 'ws://localhost:1337/';
this.socket = new WebSocket(WS_URL);

Initialize to null and add a guard:
zahlungsempfaenger_selected: null,
